## 1. English Translation

**Wei Wu Hou** (魏武侯) was deliberating affairs of state and his decisions were appropriate. None of his ministers could match his wisdom. After leaving the court, he wore a pleased expression on his face.

**Wu Qi** (吳起) then approached and said: "Have you ever heard the words of King Zhuang of Chu from anyone?"

Wu Hou asked: "What did King Zhuang of Chu say?"

Wu Qi replied: "King Zhuang of Chu deliberated affairs of state and his decisions were appropriate. None of his ministers could match his wisdom. After leaving the court, he wore a worried expression.

**Shen Gong Wu Chen** (申公巫臣) asked: 'Your Majesty, why do you look worried after the morning court?'

The King said: 'I deliberated affairs and my decisions were appropriate, yet none of my ministers can match me—that is why I am worried. In the sayings of the court musicians, it is said: "A ruler who gains a teacher becomes a king; a ruler who gains friends becomes a hegemon; a ruler who gains capable counselors survives; a ruler who relies only on himself and has no one better than himself will perish." Now, considering my own lack of virtue, and that none of my ministers can match me—is my state not on the verge of ruin? That is why I worry.'

King Zhuang worried because of this, yet you, My Lord, are pleased."

Wei Wu Hou paused, then bowed twice and said: "It is Heaven that has sent you, Master, to correct my faults."

